{"id":"36d4d756-f8d3-48e9-8382-b8fe6cfe4dfd","title":"1511/01/10","type":"main-list-block","children":[{"id":"3319df0c-d67f-4388-93f9-23c62d0bfcdc","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"From Rome, January 10th, [1511].","standoffProperties":[{"id":"403f5526-d1b7-4d09-8523-8ac91617b107","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":5,"end":8,"value":"501a8a32-2c8a-4934-9060-8c7e36339f0f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"9130a579-c2b2-4443-b83a-ff3bd09bb7e5","type":"codex/time-reference","start":11,"end":30,"value":"fad310f9-fb62-47fd-b9af-df7c66d47fa5","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"994e515f-8e2c-41a5-a9a6-f322d7b827d2","type":"style/superscript","start":21,"end":23,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"a74fd747-7d70-4088-ad76-eb503193b349","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"To Buonarroto di Lodovico Simoni,","standoffProperties":[{"id":"8efb22f2-5215-4afd-a5d7-bcd9f0dd1a02","type":"style/italics","start":0,"end":31,"value":null,"zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"59d074da-3ab8-4473-a7c1-8967746502b6","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":31,"value":"eb5c2755-f869-4ca7-8733-1c39b95bc7a0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"04e3038f-4b48-4715-8f17-62028fc28276","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"in Florence.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"b98ef7a7-eb6f-4b60-849f-17775b7cf97d","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":3,"end":10,"value":"671ee7e7-ae1b-4a5a-9591-b40203d5108f","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]}],"blockProperties":[]},{"id":"2ea3a75a-21f8-4331-99ad-fdfa54a69b47","type":"standoff-editor-block","text":"Buonarroto,\u00A0\u2014\u00A0Some days ago I received a letter from thee setting forth thy views in detail: and as it would be a lengthy matter to reply in full to all\u00A0thou sayest, I will tell thee briefly what I think. With regard to the shop, I am minded to do all I promised you as soon as I return to Florence: and although I wrote saying this was the time to invest\u00A0in a piece of land, I am still inclined to buy the shop, because when I have finished my work here and have received all that will then be due to me there will be enough to allow of my keeping my promises to you. As to thy being able to find someone now who will lend thee two or three thousand ducats for opening a shop, this must be a man with a longer purse than mine. I think thou shouldst by all means\u00A0accept the offer, but have a care that thou be not\u00A0deceived, for people are not inclined to do good to any but themselves. Thou sayest this man desires\u00A0to give thee one of his daughters to wife, and I tell thee that all the offers he has made will fall to the ground\u00A0\u2014\u00A0except the wife\u00A0\u2014\u00A0when thou hast gotten her set fast upon thy back: her thou wilt find cling to thee more closely than thou desirest. And further\u00A0more, I tell thee I do not like these rapacious dealings with men whose code of morals is lower than thine own. Avarice is a grievous sin, and nought that is concerned with sin can come to a good ending. My advice is that thou shouldst speak him fair and keep the matter open until I have finished here, when I shall know how I am situated. This will be within three months, or thereabouts. For the present act as seemeth to thee best. I was unable to reply\u00A0before.","standoffProperties":[{"id":"eb36553e-a5e1-442d-a6ac-09b10dff15ba","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":0,"end":9,"value":"eb5c2755-f869-4ca7-8733-1c39b95bc7a0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"e9b54ebd-e683-423b-9d7d-15556fb75cd4","type":"codex/claim-reference","start":14,"end":56,"value":"06184c81-586d-4171-a76e-1f3f251165bc","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"8966f457-9133-48ee-bc9b-57ba9cbe890a","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":28,"end":28,"value":"add92e01-cefe-4f13-94dd-f00eb82155b0","zeroPoint":false,"metadata":[]},{"id":"5b51cf05-a1b9-49f4-ac99-695b0e841da5","type":"codex/entity-reference","start":41,"end":4